-- Ukraine’s Six-Month State Budget Gap Narrows, Ministry Says
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2012-08-01T15:39:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-01/ukraine-s-six-month-state-budget-gap-narrows-ministry-says.html
Ukraine’s first-half state budget
deficit narrowed from a year earlier as revenue rose 16.9
percent, the  Finance Ministry  said.  The shortfall was 6.7 billion hryvnia ($826 million),
compared with 10.96 billion hryvnia in the same period of 2011,
the ministry, based in the capital, Kiev, said today in a
statement on its  website . Revenue increased to 162.96 billion
hryvnia from 139.35 billion, the ministry said.  Ukraine raised 5.09 billion hryvnia from January to June by
selling state assets, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
